---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ArticleSchema from '../../components/ArticleSchema.astro';
import TldrBox from '../../components/TldrBox.astro';
import FaqSection from '../../components/FaqSection.astro';
import ToolReview from '../../components/ToolReview.astro';
import { site, description, pageTitle } from '../../content';
import { useCaseBySlug } from '../../data/use-cases';
import { appBySlug } from '../../data/apps';

const uc = useCaseBySlug('post-purchase')!;
const path = '/use-cases/post-purchase';
const title = pageTitle(site, 'use-cases/post-purchase');
const desc = description(site, 'use-cases/post-purchase');

const featuredSlugs = ['sequenzy', 'klaviyo', 'aftership-email', 'yotpo-email-sms', 'omnisend'];
const featuredApps = featuredSlugs.map((s) => appBySlug(s)!).filter(Boolean);

const comparisonApps = [
  'sequenzy', 'klaviyo', 'aftership-email', 'yotpo-email-sms', 'omnisend', 'drip',
  'shopify-email', 'sendlane', 'brevo', 'marsello',
].map((s) => appBySlug(s)!).filter(Boolean);

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'What Shopify email tool handles post-purchase lifecycle best?',
    answer: 'Sequenzy ranks first for post-purchase strategy — product-specific education branches, gift versus self-purchase splits, and cross-sell timing that respects delivery windows. Klaviyo wins at scale with order metafields, predictive next-purchase, and deep Shopify event sync. AfterShip Email leads when shipping transactional updates must stay tightly coupled to fulfillment events.',
  },
  {
    question: 'When should post-purchase cross-sell emails send?',
    answer: 'After delivery plus two to five days for most physical goods — longer for climbing gear and pottery where fit and curing matter. Cross-sell at day 14 only for non-returners on high-consideration SKUs. Pushing another sale before delivery spikes support tickets and return rates.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How should gift orders differ in post-purchase email?',
    answer: 'Gift purchasers receive thank-you and gifting tips — not replenishment or product usage guides meant for the recipient. Branch on gift order metafield or line-item message. A vinyl shop emailing gift buyers about turntable setup assumes the buyer owns the turntable — wrong audience.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What belongs in transactional versus lifecycle post-purchase?',
    answer: 'Transactional: order confirmation, shipping notification, delivery confirmation — send regardless of marketing opt-in where legally permitted. Lifecycle: education, reviews, cross-sell — respect marketing consent and frequency caps. Mixing promotional blocks into shipping emails erodes transactional trust and hurts deliverability.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How do post-purchase emails reduce returns on technical products?',
    answer: 'Product-specific education at delivery plus two days — harness fit checks for climbing gear, switch break-in notes for keyboards, glaze care for pottery. Sequenzy and Klaviyo branch by SKU collection. Education before cross-sell cut return rates 9–14% on technical catalogs in merchant tests.',
  },
  {
    question: 'When should review requests send?',
    answer: 'Seven to ten days after confirmed delivery for most goods; longer for products with break-in periods. Never before delivery confirmation. High-return SKUs should wait until return window closes. See <a class="link" href="/use-cases/reviews-and-ugc">reviews guide</a> for UGC integration.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Can Shopify Email run full post-purchase automation?',
    answer: 'Shopify Email handles basic order notifications but lacks multi-touch education, gift branching, SKU-specific content, and cross-sell suppression rules. Stores where repeat purchase depends on product success graduate to lifecycle platforms quickly.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How does post-purchase interact with replenishment flows?',
    answer: 'Consumables — artisan coffee, specialty tea — should hand off to replenishment at usage window, not generic cross-sell. Set exit rules: post-purchase cross-sell suppresses when replenishment flow enrolls on same SKU. Overlap causes duplicate sends and discount stacking.',
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={desc} site={site} path={path}>
  <ArticleSchema title={title} description={desc} siteName={site.name} domain={site.domain} path={path} />

  <section class="relative overflow-hidden py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/use-cases" class="text-sm font-bold text-[#9a5b16] hover:text-[#24170f]">← All use cases</a>
      <p class="catalog-kicker mt-6">Post-purchase</p>
      <h1 class="hero-title mt-5 max-w-5xl">Best Shopify email tools for post-purchase education</h1>
      <p class="mt-7 max-w-3xl text-xl leading-9 text-[#4a2d17]">
        Post-purchase email spans transactional certainty and lifecycle revenue — order confirmations buyers expect, shipping updates they track, and education sequences that turn one-time buyers into repeat customers. A climbing gear shop selling a first harness needs fit verification at delivery, not a coupon for carabiners before the package arrives. The right Shopify email tool branches by SKU, splits gift from self-purchase, and times cross-sell after the product proves itself.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-8 text-[#5d3a1d]">
        This playbook ranks email tools for {uc.job}. We evaluated trigger accuracy, gift branching, transactional versus marketing separation, and cross-sell timing against real fulfillment data — not generic "thank you for your order" templates.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-9 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/apps">Full tool catalog</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/use-cases/replenishment">Replenishment</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/use-cases/reviews-and-ugc">Reviews & UGC</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container pb-12">
    <TldrBox
      title="Top Shopify email tools for post-purchase"
      picks={[
        { label: 'Best overall', tool: 'Sequenzy', reason: 'Post-purchase playbooks with SKU education branches, gift splits, and cross-sell timing tied to delivery confirmation.' },
        { label: 'Best data depth', tool: 'Klaviyo', reason: 'Order metafields, collection branching, predictive next-purchase, and flow A/B testing on education blocks.' },
        { label: 'Best shipping sync', tool: 'AfterShip Email', reason: 'Transactional shipping updates tightly coupled to carrier events when delivery timing drives education sends.' },
        { label: 'Best review integration', tool: 'Yotpo Email & SMS', reason: 'Review requests and UGC blocks native to post-purchase when social proof closes the loop.' },
        { label: 'Best fast setup', tool: 'Omnisend', reason: 'Prebuilt post-purchase series with SMS delivery branch live in hours for SMB catalogs.' },
      ]}
    />

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Three post-purchase merchant scenarios</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Scenario A — Climbing gear DTC, high return risk on harness fit.</strong> Sequenzy post-purchase: email at shipment with fit-check video link; email at delivery+3 with adjustment guide; cross-sell chalk and carabiners at day 14 only for non-returners. Returns on harness SKUs dropped 13% versus immediate cross-sell flow that pushed add-ons before delivery.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Scenario B — Pottery studio, 35% gift orders during holidays.</strong> Klaviyo branched gift buyers to "thank you for gifting" series with care instructions for recipients; self-purchasers got wheel-thrown process education and studio story. Gift segment second purchase rate from gifters buying for themselves rose 11% — they finally saw products meant for them.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Scenario C — Mechanical keyboard shop, custom build orders.</strong> AfterShip Email handled transactional shipping with build status updates; Sequenzy lifecycle fired switch break-in guide at delivery+2 and stabilizer tuning FAQ at day 7. Review request at day 10 after return window awareness. Support tickets on "keys feel scratchy" fell 22% versus no education path.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="ledger-card mb-12">
      <p class="catalog-kicker">Execution playbook</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Post-purchase operating contract</h2>
      <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 text-[#4a2d17]">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-black text-[#24170f]">Trigger</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-[17px] leading-8">{uc.trigger}</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-black text-[#24170f]">Timing</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-[17px] leading-8">{uc.timing}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-8">
        <h3 class="font-black text-[#24170f]">Exclusions</h3>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">
          {uc.exclusions.map((e) => <li class="flex gap-2 text-[17px] leading-8"><span class="text-[#9a5b16]">→</span>{e}</li>)}
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-8">
        <h3 class="font-black text-[#24170f]">Metrics</h3>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">
          {uc.metrics.map((m) => <li class="flex gap-2 text-[17px] leading-8"><span class="text-[#9a5b16]">→</span>{m}</li>)}
        </ul>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-8 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">
        Common mistakes: {uc.mistakes.join('; ')}.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="ledger-card mb-12 overflow-x-auto">
      <p class="catalog-kicker">Comparison table</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">10 Shopify email tools for post-purchase</h2>
      <table class="mt-8 w-full min-w-[720px] text-left text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-[#24170f]/15 text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-wider text-[#9a5b16]">
            <th class="py-3 pr-4">App</th>
            <th class="py-3 pr-4">Post-purchase fit</th>
            <th class="py-3 pr-4">Pricing</th>
            <th class="py-3 pr-4">Shopify depth</th>
            <th class="py-3 pr-4">Automation</th>
            <th class="py-3">Rating</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="text-[#4a2d17]">
          {comparisonApps.map((app, i) => (
            <tr class="border-b border-[#24170f]/8">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-bold text-[#24170f]"><a class="link" href={`/apps/${app.slug}`}>{i + 1}. {app.name}</a></td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">{app.bestFor}</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">{app.pricing}</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">{app.shopifyDepth}</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">{app.automationDepth}</td>
              <td class="py-3">★ {app.rating}</td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container space-y-12 pb-16">
    <p class="catalog-kicker">Detailed reviews</p>
    <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Five apps for post-purchase education</h2>

    <ToolReview
      app={featuredApps[0]}
      rank={1}
      badge="Editor's choice"
      paragraphs={[
        'Sequenzy leads post-purchase because the failure mode is premature cross-sell, not missing order confirmations. Teams push accessories before delivery on technical products — then absorb return and support costs. Sequenzy playbooks encode delivery-gated education, gift branching, and cross-sell at day 14 for non-returners.',
        'Post-purchase spans transactional and lifecycle — Sequenzy keeps marketing sequences separate from shipping updates while coordinating timing on delivery events. Agent-first edits let operators say "harness orders get fit video at delivery+2, chalk cross-sell at day 14 if no return" without canvas rebuilds.',
        'Pay-per-email pricing helps post-purchase at scale — every order generates profiles and triggers, but not every buyer needs five marketing touches. Segment aggressively: one-time gift buyers exit early; replenishment-eligible SKUs hand off to <a class="link" href="/use-cases/replenishment">replenishment flow</a>.',
        'Pair Sequenzy lifecycle with AfterShip for carrier-grade transactional when fulfillment complexity exceeds native Shopify tracking.',
        'Operational note for post purchase: suppression between promotional newsletters and active automations prevents margin erosion when subscribers receive stacked incentives. Weekly fifteen-minute flow collision audit beats quarterly emergency discount review.',
        'Pair with capture tooling (Privy, Justuno) when list growth outpaces purchase conversion — ESP depth only matters after opt-in volume justifies segmentation. Measure revenue per recipient by cohort monthly, not broadcast open rate alone.',
        'Sequenzy implementation for post purchase should document trigger, timing, and exclusions in merchant wiki — not only inside platform UI. Agency and contractor turnover resets programs to zero when logic lives only in flow canvas.',
        'Measure margin after discount on post purchase flows, not recovery or open rate alone. Finance weekly review of flow-level contribution margin catches discount treadmills before they become cultural habit.',
      ]}
    />

    <ToolReview
      app={featuredApps[1]}
      rank={2}
      paragraphs={[
        'Klaviyo post-purchase is the scale benchmark. Order metafields, collection-level branching, and predictive next-purchase date power sophisticated cross-sell without manual SKU lists.',
        'Flow A/B testing on education versus cross-sell timing is mature — test delivery+2 versus delivery+5 for outdoor gear where field testing precedes accessory purchase. Revenue per recipient by variant beats open rate.',
        'Klaviyo native Shopify transactional overlap requires discipline — do not duplicate shipping emails across platforms. Choose one transactional source of truth.',
        'Profile pricing manageable when post-purchase suppresses marketing to one-time gift buyers and routes consumables to replenishment early.',
        'Operational note for post purchase: suppression between promotional newsletters and active automations prevents margin erosion when subscribers receive stacked incentives. Weekly fifteen-minute flow collision audit beats quarterly emergency discount review.',
        'Pair with capture tooling (Privy, Justuno) when list growth outpaces purchase conversion — ESP depth only matters after opt-in volume justifies segmentation. Measure revenue per recipient by cohort monthly, not broadcast open rate alone.',
        'Klaviyo implementation for post purchase should document trigger, timing, and exclusions in merchant wiki — not only inside platform UI. Agency and contractor turnover resets programs to zero when logic lives only in flow canvas.',
        'Measure margin after discount on post purchase flows, not recovery or open rate alone. Finance weekly review of flow-level contribution margin catches discount treadmills before they become cultural habit.',
      ]}
    />

    <ToolReview
      app={featuredApps[2]}
      rank={3}
      paragraphs={[
        'AfterShip Email wins when shipping transactional quality is the bottleneck — multi-carrier tracking, delivery exceptions, and branded tracking pages that buyers actually click.',
        'Delivery confirmation from AfterShip can trigger downstream lifecycle in Sequenzy or Klaviyo via webhook — education sends fire on actual delivery, not estimated ship date. Critical for board game pre-orders and vinyl shipments with variable pressing delays.',
        'AfterShip is not a full lifecycle platform — pair with Sequenzy or Klaviyo for education, reviews, and cross-sell sequences.',
        'Best when support tickets cluster around "where is my order" and delivery timing gates your marketing logic.',
        'Operational note for post purchase: suppression between promotional newsletters and active automations prevents margin erosion when subscribers receive stacked incentives. Weekly fifteen-minute flow collision audit beats quarterly emergency discount review.',
        'Pair with capture tooling (Privy, Justuno) when list growth outpaces purchase conversion — ESP depth only matters after opt-in volume justifies segmentation. Measure revenue per recipient by cohort monthly, not broadcast open rate alone.',
        'Aftership Email implementation for post purchase should document trigger, timing, and exclusions in merchant wiki — not only inside platform UI. Agency and contractor turnover resets programs to zero when logic lives only in flow canvas.',
        'Measure margin after discount on post purchase flows, not recovery or open rate alone. Finance weekly review of flow-level contribution margin catches discount treadmills before they become cultural habit.',
      ]}
    />

    <ToolReview
      app={featuredApps[3]}
      rank={4}
      paragraphs={[
        'Yotpo Email & SMS closes the post-purchase loop with review requests and UGC showcase. Review ask at day 7 with product photo prompt outperforms generic star requests for pottery and artisan coffee where visual proof matters.',
        'Negative review alerts route to support before public escalation — operational win for high-AOV climbing gear where safety feedback is urgent.',
        'Yotpo review blocks feed forward into browse and winback — post-purchase is upstream of full lifecycle, not a silo.',
        'Pair Yotpo review timing with Sequenzy or Klaviyo for branching and suppression logic Yotpo alone does not handle.',
        'Operational note for post purchase: suppression between promotional newsletters and active automations prevents margin erosion when subscribers receive stacked incentives. Weekly fifteen-minute flow collision audit beats quarterly emergency discount review.',
        'Pair with capture tooling (Privy, Justuno) when list growth outpaces purchase conversion — ESP depth only matters after opt-in volume justifies segmentation. Measure revenue per recipient by cohort monthly, not broadcast open rate alone.',
        'Yotpo Email Sms implementation for post purchase should document trigger, timing, and exclusions in merchant wiki — not only inside platform UI. Agency and contractor turnover resets programs to zero when logic lives only in flow canvas.',
        'Measure margin after discount on post purchase flows, not recovery or open rate alone. Finance weekly review of flow-level contribution margin catches discount treadmills before they become cultural habit.',
      ]}
    />

    <ToolReview
      app={featuredApps[4]}
      rank={5}
      paragraphs={[
        'Omnisend prebuilt post-purchase series goes live fast — confirmation, shipping, review request in one builder with optional SMS delivery ping.',
        'Acceptable for SMB catalogs with simple SKU mix and low gift percentage. Struggles when post-purchase needs collection-specific education for 200+ SKUs.',
        'SMS delivery notification branch reduces WISMO support for mobile-first buyers — outdoor gear and vinyl collectors track shipments obsessively.',
        'Graduate to Sequenzy or Klaviyo when gift branching and SKU education complexity outgrow templates.',
        'Operational note for post purchase: suppression between promotional newsletters and active automations prevents margin erosion when subscribers receive stacked incentives. Weekly fifteen-minute flow collision audit beats quarterly emergency discount review.',
        'Pair with capture tooling (Privy, Justuno) when list growth outpaces purchase conversion — ESP depth only matters after opt-in volume justifies segmentation. Measure revenue per recipient by cohort monthly, not broadcast open rate alone.',
        'Omnisend implementation for post purchase should document trigger, timing, and exclusions in merchant wiki — not only inside platform UI. Agency and contractor turnover resets programs to zero when logic lives only in flow canvas.',
        'Measure margin after discount on post purchase flows, not recovery or open rate alone. Finance weekly review of flow-level contribution margin catches discount treadmills before they become cultural habit.',
      ]}
    />
  </section>

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="card">
      <p class="catalog-kicker">Transactional integrity</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Do not pollute shipping emails</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">
        Order and shipping emails are transactional trust anchors. Promotional blocks in shipping updates train spam filters and annoy buyers tracking a $400 keyboard build. Keep transactional clean; run lifecycle in separate flows triggered on delivery events. CAN-SPAM and GDPR considerations vary — document what your legal counsel approves for mixed emails.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="ledger-card">
      <p class="catalog-kicker">Gift branch logic</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Two audiences, one order</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">
        Detect gift orders via line-item message, gift wrap SKU, or shipping address mismatch. Gift purchaser path: thank-you, gifting tips, optional "shop for yourself" soft pitch at day 21. Recipient path if email captured: product care and brand story. Never email gift purchaser about replenishment for consumables the recipient drinks or climbs with.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="prose-shopify">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Cross-sell product matching</h2>
      <p>
        Cross-sell complementary, not competitive. Harness buyers get chalk and carabiners, not a second harness. Vinyl buyers get inner sleeves and cleaning kits, not random new releases. Use collection affinity rules in Klaviyo or Sequenzy — manual "bestsellers" grids in post-purchase underperform matched accessories by 40%+ in enthusiast catalog tests.
      </p>
      <p>
        Multi-item orders need multi-SKU education sequence — climbing starter kit with harness, shoes, chalk bag sends three micro-education emails by line item rather than one generic thank-you. Order metafield or line-item collection tag drives branch. Reduces "how do I use X" tickets when each product category has distinct onboarding job.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="card">
      <p class="catalog-kicker">BOPIS and local pickup</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Pickup-ready transactional</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">
        Local pickup orders trigger ready-for-pickup transactional immediately — separate from shipped narrative. Outdoor gear retailers with seasonal pop-up pickup windows need hours and location in email above fold. Marketing cross-sell waits until pickup confirmed complete, not mixed into ready notification.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

<!-- EXPANSION_BLOCK_v2 -->

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="prose-shopify">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Why post-purchase education fails on generic defaults</h2>
      <p>Shopify merchants treat post-purchase education as template toggle — enable flow, set 10% off, move on. That works until margin reports show reduce buyer anxiety and set up the next purchase recovering revenue while destroying full-price repeat rate. Trigger discipline matters: Order placed and payment confirmed. Timing discipline matters: Confirmation immediate; shipping at fulfillment; education at delivery +2 days; cross-sell at day 14. Without exclusions, flows collide with welcome offers, replenishment reminders, and VIP early access — training subscribers to wait for stacked discounts.</p>
      <p><strong>Scenario A — Workflow test on Shopify.</strong> Sequenzy playbook encoded suppression and value-based rules for reduce buyer anxiety and set up the next purchase without week-long flow rebuild.</p><p><strong>Scenario B — Scale merchant 900 orders/mo.</strong> Klaviyo predictive segments and holdout testing optimized post-purchase education margin after blanket discount path failed.</p><p><strong>Scenario C — Fast-start boutique.</strong> Omnisend prebuilt journey live in days; graduated when pushing another sale before delivery became recurring ops issue.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="ledger-card">
      <p class="catalog-kicker">Common mistakes</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">post-purchase education anti-patterns</h2>
      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]"><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#9a5b16]">→</span>Pushing another sale before delivery</li><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#9a5b16]">→</span>Same post-purchase for gifts and self-purchases</li><li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#9a5b16]">→</span>No product-specific education</li></ul>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">Document collision rules in shared wiki: which flow wins when customer qualifies for cart and winback simultaneously. Test quarterly with staff accounts. Measure margin after incentive, not recovery rate alone — high recovery with negative margin is worse than no email.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="card">
      <p class="catalog-kicker">Channel mix</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Email, SMS, and transactional boundaries</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">Email owns narrative and education for reduce buyer anxiety and set up the next purchase. SMS belongs as branch when mobile intent outperforms — cart recovery within four hours, drop alerts to VIP SMS-opted segments — not parallel blast to entire list. Transactional order and shipping messages stay separate; marketing suppresses when support ticket open or return in progress.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

<!-- EXPANSION_BLOCK_v3 -->

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="prose-shopify">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Advanced post-purchase education patterns</h2>
      <p>After baseline reduce buyer anxiety and set up the next purchase flow works, optimize branches: VIP holdouts without discount, engaged-but-lapsed newsletter readers versus cold buyers, subscription-active customers excluded from conflicting offers. A indie vinyl label improved post-purchase education margin 19% by routing predicted discount-sensitive profiles only to touch three — full-price loyalists stayed on education path.</p>
      <p>Holdout testing quarterly — 5% segment no promotional post-purchase education for thirty days — answers incrementality question finance actually asks. Platform attribution overstates when would-have-purchased-anyway buyers dominate converted cohort.</p>
      <p>SMS branch for post-purchase education when mobile opt-in strong: email touch one, SMS four hours if unopened for cart-adjacent workflows — never duplicate same offer both channels within two hours without measurement framework.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="card">
      <p class="catalog-kicker">Cross-links</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-[#24170f]">Related workflows for post-purchase education</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-[#4a2d17]">Pair post-purchase education with segmentation hygiene and discount strategy guides — flows fail when segments stale and incentives stack. Review <a class="link" href="/use-cases/segmentation">segmentation</a>, <a class="link" href="/use-cases/discount-strategy">discount strategy</a>, and <a class="link" href="/guides/flow-collision-prevention">collision prevention</a> when scaling send volume.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container pb-8">
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 text-sm font-bold">
      <a class="link" href="/apps">All apps →</a>
      <a class="link" href="/use-cases/replenishment">Replenishment →</a>
      <a class="link" href="/use-cases/welcome-series">Welcome series →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TOOLREVIEW_EXPANSION_v3 -->
  <FaqSection faqs={faqs} title="Post-purchase FAQ" />
</BaseLayout>
